name: North Central Health
tweet: Your quit attempt will be more successful if you quit with a friend. Find one to do it with you and you’ll both be better off. For free help call the Nebraska Tobacco Quitline at 1-800-QUIT-NOW.  https://t.co/UMI8XHXvYu

name: North Central Health
tweet: Becky started smoking cigarettes in high school and now suffers from chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). This COPD Awareness Month, make a plan to quit smoking and reduce your risk for respiratory diseases. #CDCTips #NEQuitline  https://t.co/gm20Am2VgY

name: North Central Health
tweet: It is best to quit smoking before you get pregnant, but if you are already pregnant quitting can still help protect you and your baby from complications. #WorldPrematurityDay #NEQuitline #CDCTips  https://t.co/KYtQFmzBxq

name: North Central Health
tweet: Veterans know when facing a challenge, having a plan, a team and the right tools are important. It’s the same thing when quitting tobacco. Call 1-800-QUIT-NOW to find the right tools for you. #VeteransDay #ThankYouForYourService #NEQuitline  https://t.co/rFo2W2yZuY

name: North Central Health
tweet: November: Lung Cancer Awareness Month - After decades of cigarette use, Rose developed lung cancer. Rose was able to quit, but in the end, it was too late and smoking ended up costing Rose her life. #CDCTips #NEQuitline  #LungCancerAwarenessMonth  https://t.co/CrbcNJDIdA
